Creating a landing page for a real estate website using Astro involves several components. Below is a production-ready Astro component named `Menu` along with a basic structure for the landing page including `Hero`, `Testimonials`, `Pricing`, and `Footer` components.

First, let's create the `Menu` component:

jsx
// src/components/Menu.astro
---
const menuItems = [
  { name: 'Home', href: '#' },
  { name: 'Properties', href: '#properties' },
  { name: 'Testimonials', href: '#testimonials' },
  { name: 'Pricing', href: '#pricing' },
  { name: 'Contact', href: '#contact' },
];
---

<nav class="bg-white shadow-md">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="flex justify-between h-16">
      <div class="flex">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center">
          <a href="#" class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800">RealEstate</a>
        </div>
        <div class="hidden sm:ml-6 sm:flex sm:space-x-8">
          {menuItems.map((item) => (
            <a
              href={item.href}
              class="border-transparent text-gray-500 hover:border-gray-300 hover:text-gray-700 inline-flex items-center px-1 pt-1 border-b-2 text-sm font-medium"
            >
              {item.name}
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</nav>


